<item>
            <title>[LU-8690] Lustre-2.5.3 with MLNX_OFED_LINUX-3.3-1.0.4.0</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-8690</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Hi Team,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We are building lustre client for our production environment along with a MLNX stack, but we are getting below mention error&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;#checking if quadrics kernel headers are present... no&lt;br/&gt;
#checking whether to use Compat RDMA... yes&lt;br/&gt;
#checking whether to use any OFED backport headers... no&lt;br/&gt;
#checking whether to enable OpenIB gen2 support... no&lt;br/&gt;
#configure: error: can&apos;t compile with OpenIB gen2 headers under /usr/src/ofa_kernel-3.3&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The environment details are given below:&lt;br/&gt;
Operating System: CentOS&lt;br/&gt;
Kernel: 2.6.32-573.el6.x86_64&lt;br/&gt;
IB Stack: Mellanox-3.3-1.0.4.0&lt;br/&gt;
Reproducible: Yes&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Method:&lt;br/&gt;
git clone git://git.whamcloud.com/fs/lustre-release.git&lt;br/&gt;
git checkout 2.5.3&lt;br/&gt;
sh autogen.sh&lt;br/&gt;
./configure --disable-server --with-o2ib=/usr/src/mlnx-ofa_kernel-3.3&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;looking for your response...&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thank You&lt;br/&gt;
Atul Yadav &lt;/p&gt;</description>
